ord time of 57.33 seconds with Smith 0.33 seconds behind.\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1802, \"end\": 1812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999836911922322, \"rank\": 9.070459791423352e-06, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 50-metre mark\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1713}, {\"ngram\": \"Smith\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1720}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1736}, {\"ngram\": \"McKeown\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1749}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 1782, \"to\": 1796}, {\"ngram\": \"the turbo power\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1838}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic record time\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1890}, {\"ngram\": \"57.33 seconds\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1907}, {\"ngram\": \"Smith\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1918}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Ultimately, I think other people's performances are completely out of my control and Kaylee is\\u2026 one-on-one, she is an absolutely incredible racer and she knows what to do when it matters, but I am really proud of myself,\\\" said the American.\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 2182, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2173, \"end\": 2181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999754561928762, \"rank\": 1.4755032191138317e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other people's performances\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1989}, {\"ngram\": \"my control\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2022}, {\"ngram\": \"Kaylee\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2033}, {\"ngram\": \"an absolutely incredible racer\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2087}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Katharine Berkoff of the United States, who had threatened an upset, had to settle for bronze.\", \"from\": 2184, \"to\": 2278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2184, \"end\": 2201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katharine Berkoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\"}, {\"begin\": 2209, \"end\": 2222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998907537762, \"rank\": 7.514288908795732e-08, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an upset\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2251}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 2271, \"to\": 2277}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Wiffen had talked ahead of his final about how he would be happy with any medal, especially given that Ireland had never had any kind of podium finish in men's swimming.\", \"from\": 2280, \"to\": 2460, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2394, \"end\": 2401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9105026045919286, \"rank\": 0.054296114684635834, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wiffen\", \"from\": 2291, \"to\": 2297}, {\"ngram\": \"any medal\", \"from\": 2361, \"to\": 2370}, {\"ngram\": \"any kind\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2424}, {\"ngram\": \"podium finish\", \"from\": 2428, \"to\": 2441}, {\"ngram\": \"men's swimming\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2459}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he delivered an epic finish to leave Tokyo champion Bobby Finke in second and the experienced Italian Gregorio Paltrinieri with bronze as he set a new Olympic record time of 7:38.19.\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2503, \"end\": 2508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999957132595926, \"rank\": 4.286822838216879e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2518, \"end\": 2529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bobby Finke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an epic finish\", \"from\": 2479, \"to\": 2493}, {\"ngram\": \"second\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2539}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2600}, {\"ngram\": \"a new Olympic record time\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2636}, {\"ngram\": \"7:38.19\", \"from\": 2640, \"to\": 2647}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ireland's only swimming medals had come in 1996 in Atlanta when Michelle Smith claimed three golds, so it was no surprise that a tearful Wiffen was caught up in the emotion of the occasion.\", \"from\": 2650, \"to\": 2839, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2650, \"end\": 2657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9105026045919286, \"rank\": 0.054296114684635834, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2701, \"end\": 2708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 0.9722957585163374, \"rank\": 0.02849363421925628, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/reso